    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) is a mechanically sorted example of the wide-body, naturally aspirated flat-six icon. Power is delivered via the M96/03 3.6L engine, featuring a VarioCam Plus system for an optimized torque curve. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle provides precise engagement, channeling output through a viscous-coupling AWD system. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and a recent borescope inspection confirming the integrity of the cylinder walls. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, utilizing Turbo-derived suspension geometry and 'Big Red' four-piston monoblock calipers for exceptional thermal management. Finished in Arctic Silver over black leather, this C4S offers a visceral, analog driving experience with the aerodynamic profile of the Turbo shell.",
