      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted E46 M3 featuring the high-revving S54B32 power plant. This 3.2L atmospheric straight-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and a 11.5:1 compression ratio to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Crucially, the dual-VANOS system has been serviced and the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The drivetrain consists of a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox paired with a limited-slip M Differential Lock. The suspension maintains factory-spec geometry with upgraded bushings and dampened by Bilstein B6 units, preserving the chassis's renowned communicative feedback. This is a driver-spec example where mechanical health has been prioritized over concours aesthetics.",
